<div class="module jumbotron container" style="display: none;" ng-app="myApp" ng-controller="myCtrl"> 
  <p>Itâ€™s easy to determine how much money you earn in a month, but do you really know where these inflows go towards?
Fill in this chart to see where you are financially on an average month. You can add or remove rows based on your inflows and spending habits.
</p>   
<br>
  <table class="table table-striped">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Income</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Monthly Salary (from part-time job)</td>
        <td>$ <input type="number" ng-model="monthlySalary"></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Monthly Allowance</td>
        <td>$ <input type="number" ng-model="monthlyAllowance"></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Other</td>
        <td>$ <input type="number" ng-model="other"></td>
      </tr> 
      <tr>
          <td><i>Total income</i></td>
      <td>$ {{ monthlySalary + monthlyAllowance + other }}</td>
      </tr>
     <thead>
        <br>
         <tr>
             <th>Expenses</th>
         </tr>
    </thead>
        <tr>
             <td>Food</td>
             <td>$ <input type="number" ng-model="food"></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
             <td>Clothing</td>
             <td>$ <input type="number" ng-model="clothing"></td>
      </tr>
        <tr>
             <td>Entertainment</td>
             <td>$ <input type="number" ng-model="entertainment"></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
             <td>Miscellaneous </td>
             <td>$ <input type="number" ng-model="miscellaneous"></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
          <td><i>Total expenses</i></td>
          <td>$ {{ food + clothing + entertainment + miscellaneous + expenses }} </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
          <td><strong><i>Monthly Net Income</i></strong></td>
          <td id="color_indicator">$ <strong>{{ netIncome() }}</strong> </td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
	<div style="background-color: red;" class="btn btn-primary fadeimg" onclick="next()">END</div>
</div>	